
🛡️ Cybersecurity Analyst Toolbox

A curated list of tools every cybersecurity analyst should know — from malware analysis to threat intelligence, link verification, forensics, and beyond.

🚀 Boost your efficiency and strengthen your security posture using this powerful toolbox.

⸻

📂 Table of Contents
 • 🔍 Threat Intelligence & URL Scanners
 • 🛠️ Malware Analysis Tools
 • 🧰 Network & Log Analysis
 • 🔓 Password & Credential Tools
 • 🧪 Pentesting & Vulnerability Scanners
 • 📘 Resources & Cheat Sheets

⸻

🔍 Threat Intelligence & URL Scanners

Tool Use Case Link
VirusTotal (https://www.virustotal.com/) Analyze files and URLs for viruses, worms, trojans 🔗 Visit (https://www.virustotal.com/)
URLScan.io (https://urlscan.io/) Scan and analyze websites for suspicious activity 🔗 Visit (https://urlscan.io/)
Hybrid Analysis (https://www.hybrid-analysis.com/) Malware and URL analysis powered by CrowdStrike 🔗 Visit (https://www.hybrid-analysis.com/)
Any.run (https://any.run/) Interactive malware sandbox 🔗 Visit (https://any.run/)
ThreatFox (https://threatfox.abuse.ch/) Lookup IOC and threat feeds 🔗 Visit (https://threatfox.abuse.ch/)


⸻

🛠️ Malware Analysis Tools

Tool Use Case Link
Intezer Analyze (https://analyze.intezer.com/) Identify malware code reuse and gene analysis 🔗 Visit (https://analyze.intezer.com/)
Joe Sandbox (https://www.joesandbox.com/) Deep malware behavior analysis 🔗 Visit (https://www.joesandbox.com/)
PEStudio (https://www.winitor.com/) Analyze executable files without running them 🔗 Visit (https://www.winitor.com/)
MalwareBazaar (https://bazaar.abuse.ch/) Download and analyze live malware samples 🔗 Visit (https://bazaar.abuse.ch/)


⸻

🧰 Network & Log Analysis

Tool Use Case Link
Wireshark (https://www.wireshark.org/) Network protocol analyzer 🔗 Visit (https://www.wireshark.org/)
TCPDump (https://www.tcpdump.org/) CLI packet capture tool 🔗 Visit (https://www.tcpdump.org/)
Splunk Free (https://www.splunk.com/en_us/software/splunk-free.html) Log analysis and SIEM tool 🔗 Visit (https://www.splunk.com/en_us/software/splunk-free.html)
Elastic Stack (https://www.elastic.co/elastic-stack) Log, search, and visualize threat data 🔗 Visit (https://www.elastic.co/elastic-stack)
Sysmon + LogParser (https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sysinternals/downloads/sysmon) Endpoint monitoring and forensic log generation 🔗 Visit (https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sysinternals/downloads/sysmon)


⸻

🔓 Password & Credential Tools

Tool Use Case Link
Have I Been Pwned (https://haveibeenpwned.com/) Check for exposed credentials 🔗 Visit (https://haveibeenpwned.com/)
CrackStation (https://crackstation.net/) Password hash cracking 🔗 Visit (https://crackstation.net/)
John the Ripper (https://www.openwall.com/john/) Password cracker 🔗 Visit (https://www.openwall.com/john/)
Hashcat (https://hashcat.net/hashcat/) Advanced password recovery 🔗 Visit (https://hashcat.net/hashcat/)


⸻

🧪 Pentesting & Vulnerability Scanners

Tool Use Case Link
Nmap (https://nmap.org/) Network discovery and vulnerability scanning 🔗 Visit (https://nmap.org/)
Shodan (https://www.shodan.io/) Search engine for internet-connected devices 🔗 Visit (https://www.shodan.io/)
Burp Suite (Community) (https://portswigger.net/burp) Web vulnerability scanner 🔗 Visit (https://portswigger.net/burp)
OWASP ZAP (https://www.zaproxy.org/) Web app security scanner 🔗 Visit (https://www.zaproxy.org/)
Nikto (https://cirt.net/Nikto2) Web server scanner 🔗 Visit (https://cirt.net/Nikto2)


